The Ibrox side, presently under caretaker manager Graeme Murty after Mark Warburton's departure on Friday, will find out their opponents on Tuesday, when Premiership rivals Hamilton entertain Dunfermline.
League Two outfit Clyde host Ayr of the Championship on the same night, while Hibs host Hearts the following Wednesday.
Premiership leaders Celtic will be strong favourites to progress having been drawn at home to St Mirren, who are currently bottom of the Championship.
Aberdeen, sitting second in the top-flight, host Thistle in an all-Premiership tie.
Aberdeen v Partick Thistle
Celtic v St Mirren
Hearts or Hibernian v Ayr United or Clyde
Rangers v Dunfermline Athletic or Hamilton Academical
Ties to be played over the weekend of 4/5 March.
